Optimized while statements
Fixed type mismatch in variable declaration optimizer:
- added char16, char8 and strings (32, 16, 8) to `TokenTypeCompatibility`
- fixed conversion of different sized data types
    - e.g. `let x: string16 = 8"";` is valid, but `let x: string8 = 16"";` is not
    - e.g. `let x: byte = 16'a';` is no longer valid
Added one-life if, else, elif and while statements
Refactored global variables:
- `CompilerOptions`: 
    - `verbose`: Whether to print verbose output [false]
    - `showWarnings`: Whether to show warnings [true]
    - `panic`: Whether to panic on errors (exit immediately) [true]
    - `debug`: Whether to print debug information [false]
    - `provideHelp`: Whether to tell the user about the correct syntax when they make a syntax error [true]
    - `allowLexerErrors`: Whether to allow lexer errors (if false, the lexer will panic on errors) [true]
    - `allowOptimization`: Whether to allow optimizations [true]
- `OptimizationOptions`:
    - `FastMath`: Fast math optimization options
        - `finiteMathOnly`: Whether to allow only finite math operations (no NaN or Inf) ; (x == x -> true) [false]
Added fast math optimization: finiteMathOnly:
- x == x -> true
- x != x -> false
- x && true -> x
- x && false -> false
Changed the directive from allowing a ton of syntaxes to make the language more strict and easier to parse:
- Variable declaration:
    - `let x: type = value;` -> a mutable variable declaration
    - `const x: type = value;` -> an immutable variable declaration
    - `type x = value;` -> an immutable variable declaration
Added types: int8, int16, int24, int32, int64, uint8, uint16, uint24, uint32, uint64, short, ushort, sbyte